data.chText: （大得）可以觉察到的，足以认为重要的；可观的
data.enText: large enough to be noticed or thought important

data.chText: 新的规定对大多数人将无大影响。
data.enText: The new regulations will not make an appreciable difference to most people.

data.chText: 可观的效果 / 增长 / 数量
儿童受到感染的危险性要高得多。
data.enText: The risk of infection is appreciably higher among children.

word_means: 可以觉察到的，足以认为重要的
simple_means.memory_skill: ap 表加强 + preci 价值 + able 可…的 → 能给出价值 → 可估计的

means: (大得)可以觉察到的，足以认为重要的

tr: enough to be estimated or measured
example: appreciable amounts of noxious wastes are dumped into the harbor

value.def: An appreciable amount or effect is large enough to be important or clearly noticed.

example.ex: It contains less than 1 per cent fat, an appreciable amount of protein, and a high content of minerals...
example.tran: 它所含脂肪不到1%，富含蛋白质，矿物质含量也很高。

example.ex: This has not had an appreciable effect on production.
example.tran: 此事未对生产造成显著影响。

value.tran: 可觉察的；相当大的；明显的

example.ex: Travel had not mellowed him appreciably...
example.tran: 游历并未使他明显成熟。

example.ex: Summer temperatures are appreciably more comfortable there.
example.tran: 那里夏天的气温明显舒服得多。
